<TITLE> BCL activist dies in internal clash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Panchagarh, Apr 8 (bdnews24.com)  A Chhatra League leader was killed in a clash between two factions of the ruling Awami League's student over leasing of a pond on Thursday. Police said Faruk Hossain, organising secretary of BCL Ward 1, was stabbed by his rivals during the clash at around noon. Brother of the deceased, Farid Hossain, told reporters, "The attack was launched under the lead of district AL publicity secretary Abu Towabur Rahman." He demanded arrest of the killers and their punishment. Abu Towab, however, refused the allegations, saying, "I was not even present at the spot." No case was filed till 7pm, said Panchagarh sadar police chief Md Jamiruddin. "The situation is under control, while police are under alert," he added. bdnews24
